(defn set-path-value [context path value]
  (let [command {:payload {:path path :value value}
                 :type    :set-path-value}]
    (echo-to-clients context command)))

(defn prepare-plugins [plugins]
  (when (seq plugins) (doall (map (fn [plugin]
                                    (swap! org.browjure.state/registry
                                           clojure.set/union
                                           (:expandable-symbols plugin)))
                                  (vals plugins))))
  (when (seq plugins) (install-npm-deps (vals plugins)))
  (when (seq plugins) (compile-plugins (vals plugins))))

(defn echo-to-clients
  [{:keys [connected-uids chsk-send!] :as context} command]
  ;; {:pre [@( ensure-servers)]}
  (when @recording (swap! recorded-commands conj command))
  (doseq [uid (:any @connected-uids)]
    (chsk-send! uid [:event/echo command])))

(defn run
  [context command]
  ;; {:pre [@(ensure-servers)]}
  (when (:debug command) (println "running command " command))
  ;;could use defmulti but don't like the redef behavior
  (let [{:keys [id type payload]} command]
    (case type
      :echo-to-client
      (echo-to-clients context payload)
      (println "todo impl run for " command))))

(defn init
  ([] (init {}))
  ([{:keys [plugins] :as ctx}]
   (let [packer (sente-transit/get-transit-packer :json)
         {:keys [ch-recv
                 send-fn
                 connected-uids
                 ajax-post-fn
                 ajax-get-or-ws-handshake-fn]} (sente/make-channel-socket!
                                                (get-sch-adapter)
                                                {:packer packer
                                                 :user-id-fn :client-id})
         context1    {:ring-ajax-post                ajax-post-fn
                      :ring-ajax-get-or-ws-handshake ajax-get-or-ws-handshake-fn
                      :ch-chsk                       ch-recv
                      :chsk-send!                    send-fn
                      :connected-uids                connected-uids
                      :plugins
                      (atom
                       (merge
                        {:browjure-sablono
                         {:id :browjure-sablono
                          :module '{:browjure-sablono
                                    {:entries [org.browjure.sablono.base]
                                     :depends-on #{:browjure}}}
                          :npm {:deps #{{:id "react" :version "17.0.1"}
                                        {:id "react-dom" :version "17.0.1"}
                                        {:id ""}}}
                          :namespace "browjure-sablono"}
                         :browjure
                         {:id :browjure
                          :module '{:browjure
                                    {:entries    [org.browjure.base]
                                     :depends-on #{:core}}}
                          :npm {:deps #{{:id "rxjs" :version "^7.0.0-beta.0"}
                                        {:id "shadow-cljs" :version "2.11.20"}}}
                          :namespace "browjure"}}
                        plugins))}
         http-svr    (start-web-server context1)
         context     (assoc context1 :http-svr http-svr)]
     (go-loop [evt (<! ch-recv)]
       (tap> (:event evt))
       (recur (<! ch-recv)))
     (prepare-plugins @(:plugins context1))
     (add-watch connected-uids :new-conns (new-connection-fn context))
     (-> context
         (merge (dissoc ctx :plugins))))))

(defn finish-recording []
  (reset! recording false)
  (doall
   (map-indexed
    (fn [i command]
      (with-open [out (io/output-stream
                       (str "resources/public/command-" i ".json"))]
        (t/write (t/writer out :json) command)))
    @recorded-commands))
  (spit "resources/public/commands.json" (count @recorded-commands))
  (reset! recorded-commands []))

(defn index-page [req]
  (hiccup/html
   (let [csrf-token
         ;; (:anti-forgery-token ring-req) ; Also an option
         (force anti-forgery/*anti-forgery-token*)]
     [:div
      [:div#sente-csrf-token {:data-csrf-token csrf-token}]
      [:div {:id "app"}
       "Browjure base app loaded. Start running your commands!"]
      [:script {:type "text/javascript" :src "js/core.js"}]
      [:script {:type "text/javascript" :src "js/browjure.js"}]
      [:script {:type "text/javascript" :src "js/browjure-sablono.js"}]])))

(defn send-plugin
  [{:keys [chsk-send!] :as context} connected-id plugin]
  (let [command {:type :register-plugin
                 :id (:id plugin)
                 :payload (merge (if (:namespace plugin) {:base-path (str "js/" (:namespace plugin) ".js")} {})
                                 plugin)}]
    (when @recording
      (swap! recorded-commands conj
             command))
    (when connected-id
      (chsk-send! connected-id
                  [:event/echo command]))))

(defn new-connection-fn
  [{:keys [plugins] :as context}]
  (fn [_ new old & args]
    (let [connected-id (first (clojure.set/difference (:ws @new) (:ws old)))]
      (doseq [plugin (-> @plugins
                         (dissoc :browjure)
                         (dissoc :browjure-sablono) vals)]
        (send-plugin context connected-id plugin))
      (send-plugin
       context
       connected-id {:id   "browjure"
                     :sablono
                     {:hiccup-tag->factory-symbol
                      {:hiccup-fn 'org.browjure.base/make-component
                       :hiccup-component
                       'org.browjure.base/hiccup-component}}}))))

(defmacro control [& args]
  [:control (->> (first args)
                 (map (fn [[k v]]
                        (cond
                          (keyword? v) [k `(tagged-value "fun" ~v)]
                          (and (list? v) (= (first v) 'fn))
                          [k `(tagged-value "fun" (quote ~v))]
                          :default [k v])))
                 (into {}))])

(defn register
  [{:keys [plugins] :as context} {:keys [id namespace sablono] :as plugin}]
  (swap! plugins assoc id plugin))

(defmacro wrap-prop-fns [[component-key & props]]
  `[~component-key
    ~@(map (fn [prop]
             (->> prop
                  (map (fn [[k v]]
                         (cond
                           (keyword? v) [k `(tagged-value "fun" ~v)]
                           (and (list? v) (= (first v) 'fn))
                           [k `(tagged-value "fun" (quote ~v))]
                           :default [k v])
                         ))
                  (into {})))
           props)])

(defn open-app-in-browser
  [{:keys [preferred-browser-sh-path] :as context}]
  (let [uri "http://localhost:4004"]
    (try
      (cond
        preferred-browser-sh-path
        (apply sh (conj preferred-browser-sh-path uri))
        (and (java.awt.Desktop/isDesktopSupported)
             (.isSupported (java.awt.Desktop/getDesktop) java.awt.Desktop$Action/BROWSE))
        (.browse (java.awt.Desktop/getDesktop) (java.net.URI. uri)))
      (Thread/sleep 7500)
      (catch java.awt.HeadlessException _))))

(defn compile-plugins [plugins]
  (println "building "
           (pr-str {:build-id   :browjure
                    :target     :browser
                    :output-dir "resources/public/js"
                    :asset-path "/js/"
                    :modules (apply merge
                                    (conj (map :module plugins)
                                          '{:core {:entries [cljs.core cljs.spec.alpha]}
                                            }))
                    :compiler-options {:optimizations :simple
                                       :output-feature-set :es6}}))
  (dev-api/compile*
   {:build-id   :browjure
    :target     :browser
    :output-dir "resources/public/js"
    :asset-path "/js/"
    :modules (apply merge
                    (conj (map :module plugins)
                          '{:core {:entries [cljs.core cljs.spec.alpha]}
                            }))
    :compiler-options {:optimizations :simple
                       :output-feature-set :es6}}
   {}))
